{"nodes":[{"content":"Calling SetScreenOff to enter connected standby","pos":[34,81]},{"content":"Calling SetScreenOff to enter connected standby","pos":[188,235]},{"content":"Calling SetScreenOff to enter connected standby","pos":[243,290]},{"content":"Calling the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>SetScreenOff<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> function turns the screen and backlight off, which causes the phone to enter the connected standby power state.","pos":[293,433]},{"content":"This lower power state can be helpful for testing power usage.","pos":[434,496]},{"content":"Important","pos":[500,509]},{"content":"This function is for use only in the Microsoft Manufacturing OS.","pos":[514,578]},{"pos":[661,667],"content":"Syntax"},{"pos":[800,810],"content":"Parameters"},{"content":"None","pos":[813,817]},{"pos":[915,927],"content":"Return Value"},{"content":"HRESULT","pos":[930,937]},{"pos":[1020,1027],"content":"Remarks"},{"content":"There is not an equivalent function to return the device to a full power state.","pos":[1030,1109]},{"pos":[1192,1199],"content":"Example"},{"content":"To use SetScreenOff, include the header and call without any parameters.","pos":[1202,1274]},{"pos":[1454,1466],"content":"Requirements"},{"pos":[1469,1519],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Header:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> ManufacturingConnectedStandbyControl.h"},{"pos":[1521,1574],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Library:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> ManufacturingConnectedStandbyControl.lib"}],"content":"---\nauthor: kpacquer\nDescription: Calling SetScreenOff to enter connected standby\nms.assetid: b9fddd1f-485b-4b09-9b18-93b994ebc076\nMSHAttr: 'PreferredLib:/library/windows/hardware'\ntitle: Calling SetScreenOff to enter connected standby\n---\n\n# Calling SetScreenOff to enter connected standby\n\n\nCalling the **SetScreenOff** function turns the screen and backlight off, which causes the phone to enter the connected standby power state. This lower power state can be helpful for testing power usage.\n\n**Important**  \nThis function is for use only in the Microsoft Manufacturing OS.\n\n \n\n## <span id=\"Syntax\"></span><span id=\"syntax\"></span><span id=\"SYNTAX\"></span>Syntax\n\n\n``` syntax\nHRESULT SetScreenOff();\n```\n\n## <span id=\"Parameters\"></span><span id=\"parameters\"></span><span id=\"PARAMETERS\"></span>Parameters\n\n\nNone\n\n## <span id=\"Return_Value\"></span><span id=\"return_value\"></span><span id=\"RETURN_VALUE\"></span>Return Value\n\n\nHRESULT\n\n## <span id=\"Remarks\"></span><span id=\"remarks\"></span><span id=\"REMARKS\"></span>Remarks\n\n\nThere is not an equivalent function to return the device to a full power state.\n\n## <span id=\"Example\"></span><span id=\"example\"></span><span id=\"EXAMPLE\"></span>Example\n\n\nTo use SetScreenOff, include the header and call without any parameters.\n\n``` syntax\n#include <ManufacturingConnectedStandbyControl.h>\nSetScreenOff();\n```\n\n## <span id=\"Requirements\"></span><span id=\"requirements\"></span><span id=\"REQUIREMENTS\"></span>Requirements\n\n\n**Header:** ManufacturingConnectedStandbyControl.h\n\n**Library:** ManufacturingConnectedStandbyControl.lib\n\n \n\n \n\n\n\n\n\n"}